<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: PvP isnt balanced and will be fixed</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Zorathka">Zorathka</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:22 a.m. 30/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: PvP isnt balanced and will be fixed<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1990" TARGET=_self>PvP isnt balanced and will be fixed</A> (Lanfate)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Im used to playing a online game where not only there are no PvP limits i.e a level 50 could kill a level 1 if they so wished, but also you lose half of that levels exp, that is half of the exp needed to get to the next level if you died by mob or pkill, thus if you were two bars into 17 you would go down those 2 bars and the remainder of 16, and theres no loot limit, you can lose everything. Also things like item decay, item rent etc. Also on regaining a level lost you have less hit points than you originaly had at that level.

<BR>Count yourselfs lucky that Everquest has such nice PvP rules and that it holds your hand all the way through, if they wanted to they could REALY make R.Z the Elites server. As it stands now its a very easy PvP game to play.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
